        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-04-29T11:20:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-04-29T11:20:00-05:00" n="43"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <head>43. Telegram From the Department of State to all American Republic Diplomatic
                    Posts and the U.S. Commander-in-Chief, Southern Command<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d43fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG_1"
                            >RG</gloss> 59, Central Foreign Policy File, D770150–0691. Unclassified;
                        Immediate. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_LWH_1">Luers</persName> and
                        Einaudi; cleared by <persName corresp="#p_CCA_1">Chapman</persName>;
                        approved by <persName corresp="#p_TTA_1">Todman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-04-29T16:20:00+00:00">April 29, 1977, 1620Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96982. From <persName corresp="#p_TTA_1">Todman</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJD_1">Duffey</persName>. Subject: Cultural Initiatives.</p>
                <p>1. The President said April 14 that we would develop new exchange programs, in
                    consultation with other governments and with the <gloss target="#t_OAS_1"
                        >OAS</gloss>, to improve cultural relationships in the Americas.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d43fn2">See <ref target="#d38fn2">footnote 2, Document
                        38</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>2. What scope do you believe we should give to these initiatives? What needs and
                    opportunities could be met? How could we best engage your host government,
                    institutions, and private sectors? Most importantly, how could we engage your
                    society’s creative thinkers, writers and other talents?</p>
                <p>3. We need your reply by <gloss target="#t_COB_1">COB</gloss> Wednesday May
                        4.<note n="3" xml:id="d43fn3">For the response from Mexico City, see <ref
                            target="#d45">Document 45</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Vance</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
